# ZiumSync Agent Directives

You are an advanced AI coding assistant working on the ZiumSync project.

## Critical Instructions
Before you write any code, modify any architecture, or create any tests in the `backend/` or `frontend/` directory, you **MUST** first read and strictly adhere to the rules defined in the following Playbooks:
1. **Backend:** `docs/skills/backend/SKILL.md`
2. **Frontend:** `docs/skills/frontend/SKILL.md`

Failure to follow the exact dependency management (uv), typing (mypy/ruff), database conventions (SQLModel/uuid4), and Error Handling standards outlined in the Backend Playbook will result in CI/CD pipeline failures.

## The Self-Updating Mandate
If you are tasked with implementing a **new architectural pattern**, adding a **new core dependency**, or modifying the **deployment strategy**, you MUST automatically update the relevant Playbook (`backend/SKILL.md` or `frontend/SKILL.md`) to reflect these new standards before finishing your task. You are a self-documenting agent.
